# Objects are like mini imports. 

# When you instantiate (create) a class, you get an object.


# Example:

sweets = mysweets()

sweets.sugar()

print sweets.cotton_candy




# 3 ways to get things from "sweets":


# "dict" style:

mysweets['sugar']


# module style:

mysweets.sugar()
print mysweets.cotton_candy


# class style: 

sweets = mysweets()
sweets.sugar()
print sweets.cotton_candy




